172
00:13:29,801 --> 00:13:32,194
♫ There are many stories. ♫

173
00:13:32,873 --> 00:13:36,193
♫ Each of them is very memorable. ♫

174
00:13:37,478 --> 00:13:41,233
♫ Which is the most important of all. ♫

175
00:13:44,175 --> 00:13:46,615
♫ Those saying they don't care ♫

176
00:13:47,440 --> 00:13:49,940
♫ are the one who cares the most ♫

177
00:13:49,940 --> 00:13:52,376
I don't feel like going back to my grandfather's.

178
00:13:52,376 --> 00:13:54,873
Why don't we stay in a hotel?

179
00:13:54,897 --> 00:13:56,795
♫ We used to pretend it's all coincidence ♫

180
00:13:56,795 --> 00:13:58,103
Why?

181
00:13:58,127 --> 00:14:00,819
♫ We used to fight and reconcile ♫

182
00:14:00,819 --> 00:14:03,868
I'm afraid I'll ask him after you leave.

183
00:14:03,868 --> 00:14:05,555
♫ But I forgot what I wanted. ♫

184
00:14:05,555 --> 00:14:07,016
I'm afraid he'll lie to me, too.

185
00:14:07,040 --> 00:14:10,612
♫ I forgot when it all began. ♫

186
00:14:11,679 --> 00:14:12,816
How about I take you home?

187
00:14:12,816 --> 00:14:14,028
♫ We lost to a joke ♫

188
00:14:14,052 --> 00:14:15,839
♫ We used to hug in the rain. ♫

189
00:14:15,863 --> 00:14:20,111
♫ I got sad because you're crying. ♫

190
00:14:20,135 --> 00:14:26,693
♫ I still remember every little thing you told me. ♫

191
00:14:26,717 --> 00:14:28,573
♫ It's the warm candlelight. ♫

192
00:14:28,597 --> 00:14:30,562
♫ It's our heartbeats and pulses ♫

193
00:14:30,586 --> 00:14:34,554
♫ It's the brilliant fireworks and snow. ♫

194
00:14:34,578 --> 00:14:39,899
♫ Everything written in the diary has come true. ♫

195
00:14:39,899 --> 00:14:41,899
Coming!

196
00:14:45,060 --> 00:14:47,560
Chi-Chi, you're back!

197
00:14:47,560 --> 00:14:50,216
- Hello, Uncle.
- Hello!

198
00:14:51,579 --> 00:14:53,720
Sister, you're back.

199
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:57,935
- Uncle, I'll leave now.
- Sure!

200
00:14:57,935 --> 00:15:00,675
- Thank you, Xu Fang.
- No problem!

201
00:15:34,550 --> 00:15:37,899
I have something to tell both of you.

202
00:15:38,999 --> 00:15:41,919
Go ahead, I'm listening!

203
00:15:44,139 --> 00:15:48,739
Your mother and I have divorced.

204
00:15:53,219 --> 00:15:55,620
We didn't tell you

205
00:15:55,620 --> 00:15:59,500
because, at the time, you were both still small.

206
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:03,000
We didn't want to bother you with what happened between us adults.

207
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:06,920
We didn't want to upset you and affect your studies.

208
00:16:06,920 --> 00:16:09,376
So, we decided to wait until you grew up

209
00:16:09,376 --> 00:16:12,379
and found the right time to tell you.

210
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:16,340
Do you think now is the right time?

211
00:16:17,919 --> 00:16:22,899
You both should know that no matter what happens,

212
00:16:22,899 --> 00:16:24,755
we still care about you the most.

213
00:16:24,755 --> 00:16:27,019
But you lied to us!

214
00:16:27,019 --> 00:16:30,860
Yes, we did lie to you.

215
00:16:30,860 --> 00:16:34,696
But we're trying to minimize the damage.

216
00:16:34,696 --> 00:16:38,259
We wanted to protect you from any harm

217
00:16:38,259 --> 00:16:40,820
as much as we could.

218
00:16:43,999 --> 00:16:48,240
So, you think telling us now won't do us any harm?

219
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:50,200
Chi-chi.

220
00:16:52,380 --> 00:16:54,979
I'm so sorry for both of you.

221
00:16:56,540 --> 00:16:59,739
You've been acting for ten years.

222
00:16:59,739 --> 00:17:02,535
My mother even came home once in a while.

223
00:17:02,535 --> 00:17:05,419
You've been pretending to be a model couple.

224
00:17:06,740 --> 00:17:08,640
That's so ridiculous!

225
00:17:11,080 --> 00:17:15,180
I know that you've been wishing for a reunion.

226
00:17:15,180 --> 00:17:19,900
You've been trying your best and even got into Rong University.

227
00:17:19,900 --> 00:17:23,799
You've been our mediator.

228
00:17:23,799 --> 00:17:27,559
And, and you even sent me messages on WeChat.

229
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:31,620
I thought that was a smart move.

230
00:17:33,050 --> 00:17:35,519
In fact, that's very stupid of me.

231
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:41,760
I'm sorry.

232
00:17:41,760 --> 00:17:46,000
I hope you can forgive us.

233
00:17:47,330 --> 00:17:49,680
I'm old.

234
00:17:49,680 --> 00:17:53,319
And I've come across many estranged children

235
00:17:53,319 --> 00:17:57,580
without fathers or mothers.

236
00:17:57,580 --> 00:18:01,600
They wanted to be loved and cared.

237
00:18:02,170 --> 00:18:05,259
I didn't want you to become like them.

238
00:18:05,259 --> 00:18:07,639
That's why I lied to you.

239
00:18:09,419 --> 00:18:11,960
Your mother and I,

240
00:18:14,299 --> 00:18:16,460
we have tried our best.

241
00:18:16,460 --> 00:18:18,519
Okay, I get it.

242
00:18:18,519 --> 00:18:21,856
Stop talking! Just leave me alone.

243
00:18:39,470 --> 00:18:43,419
Chi-chi, Geng-geng.

244
00:18:43,419 --> 00:18:45,400
I hope that

245
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:50,230
this conversation won't affect your lives or studies.

246
00:18:50,960 --> 00:18:54,819
Chi-chi, rest well!

247
00:19:02,840 --> 00:19:04,640
You should get out, too.

248
00:19:57,279 --> 00:19:59,715
I'm going back to the training and I'll be back in two days.

249
00:19:59,715 --> 00:20:02,100
Call me if you need me!

250
00:20:03,679 --> 00:20:05,379
Sure!

251
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:14,980
Sister, are you awake yet?

252
00:20:20,619 --> 00:20:23,360
Sister, you're awake!

253
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:32,076
Sister, it's winter break, let's hang out together.

254
00:20:32,076 --> 00:20:34,510
I don't want to.

255
00:20:34,510 --> 00:20:38,150
I've been working hard for the exam.

256
00:20:38,159 --> 00:20:40,680
I said I don't want to.

257
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:44,039
I need to catch up on sleep.

258
00:20:46,360 --> 00:20:48,460
Are you alright?

259
00:20:50,390 --> 00:20:52,680
What?

260
00:20:53,280 --> 00:20:57,780
About what dad said yesterday.

261
00:20:57,780 --> 00:20:59,579
I've forgotten that.

262
00:21:02,100 --> 00:21:04,719
Then, that's such a relief!

263
00:21:04,719 --> 00:21:06,836
I was so worried about you.

264
00:21:06,836 --> 00:21:11,520
I was afraid you'd be very upset about it.

265
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:15,479
But it seems that you're quite strong.

266
00:21:18,960 --> 00:21:21,499
You're worried about me?

267
00:21:21,499 --> 00:21:23,619
Yes.

268
00:21:23,619 --> 00:21:26,499
Although our parents have separated,

269
00:21:26,499 --> 00:21:29,319
they never stop loving us.

270
00:21:30,279 --> 00:21:32,879
You knew about the divorce all this time?

271
00:21:37,059 --> 00:21:38,759
I...

272
00:21:38,759 --> 00:21:40,660
knew...

273
00:21:40,660 --> 00:21:43,800
I did not know...

274
00:22:37,450 --> 00:22:40,380
You brought the motorbike back here?

275
00:22:40,380 --> 00:22:42,840
I didn't want to leave it at Rong City.

276
00:22:44,780 --> 00:22:46,480
I bought you this.

277
00:22:55,319 --> 00:22:56,819
Where are the questions?

278
00:23:04,639 --> 00:23:06,819
You've answered them all?

279
00:23:06,819 --> 00:23:09,980
There's nothing to do during the holiday.

280
00:23:13,780 --> 00:23:17,199
This one... I saved this question for you.

281
00:23:17,199 --> 00:23:20,475
Didn't you call yourself a top student? Solve it and explain the answer to me.

282
00:23:20,475 --> 00:23:24,579
Stop pretending! You can't solve it, can you?

283
00:23:24,579 --> 00:23:27,720
But it's the final question from the previous year exam.

284
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:31,439
It's unusually hard, so it's normal if you can't solve it.

285
00:23:31,439 --> 00:23:35,316
I should be able to solve it, I'm unusually smart after all.

286
00:23:37,260 --> 00:23:39,860
Look! Here's the solution to this question.

287
00:23:39,860 --> 00:23:43,360
First, you need to find out the gradient.

288
00:23:43,360 --> 00:23:47,479
Then, use this formula to find out the maxima and minima.

289
00:23:47,479 --> 00:23:49,439
Get it?

290
00:23:49,439 --> 00:23:53,300
This... Can you explain it again? I...

291
00:23:53,300 --> 00:23:55,020
I'm talking to you in Mandarin.

292
00:23:55,020 --> 00:23:58,080
I... I didn't get it.

293
00:23:58,600 --> 00:24:02,579
Listen carefully! First, you need to find out the gradient.

294
00:24:02,579 --> 00:24:08,260
Then, use this formula to find out the maxima and minima.

295
00:24:08,260 --> 00:24:12,480
- Get it?
- So, it was like that?

296
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:15,556
Give me that! I'll solve it.

297
00:24:18,819 --> 00:24:21,855
It's a hard question but I only explained it twice.

298
00:24:21,855 --> 00:24:26,760
You're no longer that wimpy kid who fought with me at the cafe.

299
00:24:26,760 --> 00:24:29,080
Did you just call me a wimpy kid?

300
00:24:30,980 --> 00:24:35,659
Thanks for your exercise book! Ever since I finished it, I find it easy to answer other questions.

301
00:24:35,659 --> 00:24:38,159
It's simply easy.

302
00:24:38,159 --> 00:24:41,379
What? You've got interested in math?

303
00:24:41,379 --> 00:24:45,319
Yeah! And I found I don't hate Demon He as much as I used to.

304
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:51,160
- What?
- Please respect my mother.

305
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:54,977
Since you're rebellious, I think you don't like your old-fashioned mother.

306
00:24:54,977 --> 00:24:57,480
It's okay, we're all the same.

307
00:25:00,159 --> 00:25:03,500
Didn't you say you'd give me another exercise book?

308
00:25:03,500 --> 00:25:04,878
Is she really mad at me?

309
00:25:04,878 --> 00:25:06,279
[KFC]

310
00:25:06,279 --> 00:25:11,160
Big Li! Big Li, I was wrong. Don't get mad at me.

311
00:25:15,660 --> 00:25:18,080
Big Li, wait for me!

312
00:25:19,260 --> 00:25:23,095
Big Li, wait for me! Big Li, I was wrong! Big Li!

313
00:25:23,095 --> 00:25:25,020
Big Li!

314
00:25:57,059 --> 00:25:58,759
Big Li!

315
00:26:00,699 --> 00:26:03,040
Big Li, wait for me!

316
00:26:03,040 --> 00:26:04,840
Big Li!

317
00:26:10,210 --> 00:26:12,619
- Why are you so fast?
- How did you catch up?

318
00:26:27,360 --> 00:26:30,360
- Are you okay?
- I just need some rest.

319
00:26:30,360 --> 00:26:33,339
It's a short distance, it's nothing.

320
00:26:35,080 --> 00:26:37,515
I'm sorry for what I said.

321
00:26:37,515 --> 00:26:39,439
Please accept my apology.

322
00:26:40,050 --> 00:26:42,900
A drink? That's very insincere of you.

323
00:26:49,290 --> 00:26:51,399
Why did you chase me?

324
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:54,736
You were riding your motorbike so fast.

325
00:26:54,736 --> 00:26:56,679
I was afraid you'd kill yourself.

326
00:26:56,679 --> 00:26:58,880
What if you really did that?

327
00:26:58,880 --> 00:27:03,639
Kiddo, that's just an ordinary road, not a highway.

328
00:27:03,639 --> 00:27:06,299
You ride on highways, too?

329
00:27:08,179 --> 00:27:12,339
I'm sure you ride your motorbike as fast as lightning on highways.

330
00:27:12,339 --> 00:27:14,500
Does it feel good?

331
00:27:14,500 --> 00:27:16,739
How should I put it?

332
00:27:21,219 --> 00:27:24,159
Once you feel the freedom

333
00:27:24,159 --> 00:27:26,639
of riding a motorbike,

334
00:27:28,559 --> 00:27:30,479
you won't give up on it.

335
00:27:33,860 --> 00:27:35,639
I'm not trying to annoy you.

336
00:27:35,639 --> 00:27:39,615
It's just that I noticed how dangerous you ride your motorbike.

337
00:27:39,615 --> 00:27:41,515
I was worried to death.

338
00:27:41,515 --> 00:27:43,620
You would've got yourself killed.

339
00:27:43,620 --> 00:27:46,079
My mother said the same thing.

340
00:27:46,919 --> 00:27:50,799
Demon H... Ms. He cares about you.

341
00:27:50,799 --> 00:27:53,439
And she's very proud of you.

342
00:27:55,360 --> 00:27:56,960
By the way,

343
00:27:57,699 --> 00:28:01,020
does Ms. He know about your grade retention?

344
00:28:02,399 --> 00:28:07,636
I think you should stop keeping her in the dark.

345
00:28:07,636 --> 00:28:09,900
But I have to do so.

346
00:28:11,059 --> 00:28:13,199
This is not what she wants me to be.

347
00:28:13,199 --> 00:28:16,656
Why are you saying so? She always praises you in our class.

348
00:28:16,656 --> 00:28:20,299
She calls you our role model.

349
00:28:20,299 --> 00:28:22,916
- Really?
- Really!

350
00:28:22,916 --> 00:28:25,620
And she doesn't know you gave me this exercise book.

351
00:28:25,620 --> 00:28:30,100
When she found out about it, I lied that I got it on Taobao.

352
00:28:30,100 --> 00:28:32,339
And she almost seized it.

353
00:28:32,339 --> 00:28:34,819
But she's so happy

354
00:28:34,819 --> 00:28:37,335
to see my good results.

355
00:28:37,359 --> 00:28:41,860
She said I'd improved a lot because of your exercise book.

356
00:28:43,720 --> 00:28:47,439
Tell me! What's Ms He like when she's at home?

357
00:28:50,780 --> 00:28:53,100
About the same when she's at school.

358
00:28:53,100 --> 00:28:54,980
Quite demanding as well.

359
00:28:54,980 --> 00:28:58,039
I remember when I was at Grade Three, I read a novel secretly.

360
00:28:58,039 --> 00:28:59,870
When she found out about it,

361
00:28:59,870 --> 00:29:03,620
she tore it in front of me.

362
00:29:03,620 --> 00:29:05,399
I was thinking that

363
00:29:05,399 --> 00:29:09,499
once I'd got into university, I could do whatever I wanted.

364
00:29:10,240 --> 00:29:14,860
But, now, I don't know how to face her.

365
00:29:14,860 --> 00:29:17,859
Why don't you ask for your father's help?

366
00:29:17,859 --> 00:29:20,700
He passed away when I was small.

367
00:29:21,939 --> 00:29:25,556
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay, you didn't know that.

368
00:29:26,473 --> 00:29:28,173
Oh, yeah.

369
00:29:33,279 --> 00:29:37,460
Finish this exercise book, then you can thank me.

370
00:29:38,280 --> 00:29:41,020
It's easy-peasy.

371
00:29:41,020 --> 00:29:44,919
To be honest, it's very lucky for me

372
00:29:47,039 --> 00:29:48,939
to meet you.

373
00:29:50,140 --> 00:29:52,820
Once I finish this exercise book,

374
00:29:52,820 --> 00:29:56,919
I'll lead a free life.

375
00:29:56,919 --> 00:29:59,200
Nonsense,

376
00:29:59,200 --> 00:30:03,519
this is just a ticket for you to cross the bridge, replenish your energy,

377
00:30:03,519 --> 00:30:06,020
and make you more well-equipped.

378
00:30:06,020 --> 00:30:08,539
I never thought there are so many rules in this game.

379
00:30:08,539 --> 00:30:10,539
Why didn't I know them?

380
00:30:10,539 --> 00:30:12,900
Finish your drink and we'll leave.

381
00:30:14,260 --> 00:30:16,360
Wait for me!

382
00:30:25,479 --> 00:30:27,279
What?

383
00:30:48,760 --> 00:30:51,939
- Feeling better?
- Big Li,

384
00:30:51,939 --> 00:30:55,500
you're truly my saviour.

385
00:30:55,500 --> 00:30:57,659
Don't mention it! Let's go.

386
00:30:57,659 --> 00:30:59,740
Savior! Savior, wait for me.

387
00:30:59,740 --> 00:31:01,660
Savior, don't go!

388
00:31:01,660 --> 00:31:04,699
Savior! Savior, don't go.

389
00:31:05,419 --> 00:31:09,020
Savior, I have something to tell you.

390
00:31:09,020 --> 00:31:10,800
Go ahead!

391
00:31:10,800 --> 00:31:13,480
My sister found out that

392
00:31:13,480 --> 00:31:16,880
my parents had divorced

393
00:31:17,600 --> 00:31:19,159
long ago.

394
00:31:19,159 --> 00:31:21,559
They've been keeping us in the dark.

395
00:31:21,559 --> 00:31:24,660
Actually, I knew it all along.

396
00:31:24,660 --> 00:31:28,840
But I've been pretending to know nothing

397
00:31:28,840 --> 00:31:31,819
for the sake of my sister.

398
00:31:31,819 --> 00:31:34,195
Although my sister seems to be okay with it,

399
00:31:34,195 --> 00:31:37,059
deep inside she's very upset.

400
00:31:37,059 --> 00:31:40,140
But I don't know how to comfort her.

401
00:31:40,140 --> 00:31:42,200
So, I want to ask you for a favor.

402
00:31:42,200 --> 00:31:44,279
Aren't you her roommate?

403
00:31:44,279 --> 00:31:47,240
If you have time, please talk to her.

404
00:31:47,240 --> 00:31:49,740
I find that you are more mature than her.

405
00:31:53,480 --> 00:31:55,900
It's pointless to talk to her,

406
00:31:56,490 --> 00:31:59,299
She'll be alright when the time comes.

407
00:31:59,299 --> 00:32:01,980
It's just a matter of time.

408
00:32:01,980 --> 00:32:03,920
Really?

409
00:32:05,939 --> 00:32:08,880
All your sister needs is time.

410
00:32:11,539 --> 00:32:14,119
You must be feeling upset too.

411
00:32:14,119 --> 00:32:18,819
Even though you're feeling down, you still care about your sister.

412
00:32:18,819 --> 00:32:22,439
She's so lucky to have you as her brother.

413
00:32:24,570 --> 00:32:30,720
Your parents and sister have their own ways to deal with it.

414
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:32,360
Same goes with you.

415
00:32:32,360 --> 00:32:35,779
You need to find your own way too.

416
00:32:38,200 --> 00:32:40,039
Get it?

417
00:32:46,020 --> 00:32:48,739
Wimpy kid!

418
